{
  "stem": "15174.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it would have been the greatest thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I think to myself, and now here I am.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, it's-- it's just-- it's a weird feeling.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But anyway, nobody-- no one would take us in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And of course, the Captain couldn't continue just sailing along in the Florida waters.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So finally, he set sail back to Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And-- and again, it was-- you know, people were just horrified, depressed, scared, because we knew-- I mean, we knew that if we went back to Hamburg, we would not be allowed just to go into the country and go back to where we had lived before.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We would be put in the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Now, of course, concentration camps in 1939 were not what the concentration camps were a few years later.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But they were bad enough.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we had heard stories about people who had been in concentration camps-- Jews-- and it was awfully frightening.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the trip back from Havana to Europe was the exact antithesis of the trip from Europe to Havana, because on the trip to Havana we were all happy and carefree and so on and the way back, you know, everybody was-- felt depressed.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so we were sailing, ostensibly, for Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, then-- no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Captain, he continued to meet with the committee of the passengers, but what could he tell them?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Actually, I've read that the Captain had a plan that he was not going to go back to Hamburg, but if it came to that, he would beach the boat on the English shore, and then the British would have to take us in.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Whether that's so or not, I'm not-- I don't-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I've read about it in several books.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
